<br />I want to make a cart flasher (I think?) for the Famicom so I can put stuff on cartridges.
<br />I also want to make an FC dev cart with VRC6.
<br />Eventually I want to make my own game, but for now I just want to play the VRC6 NSF's I make on actual hardware.
<br />
<br />While I've seen lots of cool stuff for the NES, like <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=47802&amp;sid=134b259aeec3c9dfe66418d46ac3a1bc" class="postlink">this thread</a>, I can't find any information for making Famicom carts.
<br />Also <a href="http://www2s.biglobe.ne.jp/~tns/" class="postlink">this</a> looked interesting, but I unfortunately cannot read Japanese, so I don't really understand if what it is.
<br />
<br />
<br />If a VRC6 cart is too difficult for a first project, I'd like to start with a normal cart.
<br />
<br />Any help would be greatly appreciated, as I really don't know what I'm talking about :D

		

