	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Is it just me or tepples makes his best attempt to disgust newcommers ?
<br />
<br />You can make an VRC6 cart, the most difficult part is probably to find one... you'd have to import one of the 3 japanese games that used it.
<br />
<br />As tepples said, the powerpak is probably the easiest/best way to go, but keep in mind that the VRC6 chip itself might not be 100% accurately emulated, it's possible that the powerpak could act differently from a real VRC, but as long as you stick to regular things, it'll be ok. If you rely on really weird "tricks" on those channels (like the semi-doccumented "direct-offset" mode of pulse channels) then you're blind without an actual VRC cart.
<br />
<br />After that it's probably not a problem to open it and replace it with wathever ROMs you want in it, as long as you don't replace them by a commercial game and sell it for a higher price (which thankfully doesn't seem to be your intentions at all) it'll be ok. It's a Konami cart, not Nintnedo so things are actually easier : You won't have to cut traces and add tiny wires.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


